zzlab","html_url":"https://github.com/bozzlab","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-10-19T17:47:22Z","updated_at":"2020-10-19T17:47:22Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"> @bozzlab How are you setting up your tracking server? Is it behind an NGINX or Apache httpd server as a proxy? This is done on the [client-side](https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/3f53b46177789924f00bae29a182f459ec123e16/mlflow/tracking/_tracking_service/utils.py#L120)\r\n\r\nThanks for reply, \r\nNo, I don't have any proxy like that for my project. \r\nBecause I used the Serverless (Cloud Run/Fergate) for deploying. \r\nThese services already had the Load balancer and proxy layer.\r\n\r\nSo the MLflow required the Nginx or Apache for authentication right? \r\nIf I don't want to work with Nginx or Apache, It's anyway to used this feature? \r\n\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/comments/712332878/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"bozzlab","id":41643434,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQxNjQzNDM0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/41643434?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bozzlab","html_url":"https://github.com/bozzlab","followers_url":"https://api.git